OL,3,CGang convicted over #200m money
OL,4,Claundering plot
OL,6,FFowler Oldfield's legitimate business
OL,7,Fwould involve the purchase of scrap
OL,8,Fjewellery, including gold, in return
OL,9,Ffor cash. However, the business model
OL,10,Fdramatically changed to receiving and
OL,11,Fprocessing cash on a large scale.
OL,13,FForensic analysis was carried out of
OL,14,Finvoices, emails and paperwork, as
OL,15,Fwell as more than 8,000 hours of CCTV
OL,16,Ffootage. It was calculated that more
OL,17,Fthan #266 million was paid into the
OL,18,FFowler Oldfield accounts from January
OL,19,F2014 to September 2016.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/9
