OL,4,Claundering plot
OL,6,FRashid was accused of collecting cash
OL,7,Fand bringing it to be laundered at
OL,8,FFowler Oldfield, with the judge saying
OL,9,Fhe provided a money laundering service
OL,10,Ffor others and was "the most likely
OL,11,Froute by which Frankel and Rawson
OL,12,Fbecame involved in money laundering".
OL,14,FBabber, who was based in London where
OL,15,Fother members of his family ran the
OL,16,F"well-known and reputable business"
OL,17,FRPS Jewellers Limited, had his own
OL,18,Fcompany called Goldsteel Limited.
